From: msedek <msedek@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Mar 2026
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] drm/probe_helper: signal hotplug for force-enabled connectors on HPD

When a connector has force == DRM_FORCE_ON (set via video=CONNECTOR:e),
check_connector_changed() calls the driver's detect() callback, which
for well-behaved drivers returns connector_status_connected regardless
of actual hardware state. This means the epoch counter never increments
and no uevent is sent to userspace.

However, the HPD interrupt itself indicates a physical state change on
the link (e.g., a TV switching inputs). Even though the logical status
stays "connected", the HDMI/DP link may need re-training. Userspace
compositors (KWin, Mutter, etc.) need to be notified so they can
trigger a modeset to re-negotiate the link.

This patch adds a force check to check_connector_changed(): when a
force-enabled connector receives an HPD event, we increment the epoch
counter and return true to ensure the hotplug uevent reaches userspace.

Note: The software polling path (output_poll_execute) already skips
force-enabled connectors. This patch addresses only the hardware HPD
IRQ path, which was previously unguarded.

Bug: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/misc/-/issues/XXXX
Signed-off-by: msedek <msedek@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_probe_helper.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_probe_helper.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_probe_helper.c
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_probe_helper.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_probe_helper.c
@@ -984,6 +984,21 @@ static bool check_connector_changed(struct drm_connector *connector)
 	old_epoch_counter = connector->epoch_counter;
 	connector->status = drm_helper_probe_detect(connector, NULL, false);

+	/*
+	 * For force-enabled connectors, the driver's detect() returns the
+	 * forced status, so the epoch counter never increments. But an HPD
+	 * event on a forced connector still indicates a physical link change
+	 * (e.g., a TV switching inputs). Notify userspace so the compositor
+	 * can trigger a modeset to re-train the link.
+	 */
+	if (connector->force && old_epoch_counter == connector->epoch_counter) {
+		connector->epoch_counter += 1;
+		drm_dbg_kms(dev,
+			    "[CONNECTOR:%d:%s] HPD on force-enabled connector, signaling change for link re-training\n",
+			    connector->base.id, connector->name);
+		return true;
+	}
+
 	if (old_epoch_counter == connector->epoch_counter) {
 		drm_dbg_kms(dev, "[CONNECTOR:%d:%s] Same epoch counter %llu\n",
 			    connector->base.id,
